on the homeless, poor sods.

101
00:07:15,259 --> 00:07:18,922
<i>[Wesley] This last victim</i>
<i>was a teenage girl. A runaway.</i>

102
00:07:19,029 --> 00:07:21,930
- She was ripped apart.
- There's not much we can do about it now, huh?

103
00:07:22,032 --> 00:07:24,796
Angel, we need to find
this demon and destroy it before...

104
00:07:24,902 --> 00:07:29,271
Somebody else dies?
Yeah, I know, Wes.

105
00:07:29,373 --> 00:07:31,341
People are dying
every day all over.

106
00:07:31,441 --> 00:07:34,171
- This girl's just one more statistic...
- Stacey.

107
00:07:34,278 --> 00:07:36,746
The statistic's name
was Stacey Bluth.

108
00:07:39,516 --> 00:07:43,077
Well, you know we can't save everybody,
and we can't sweat the small stuff.

109
00:07:43,187 --> 00:07:45,155
Small?

110
00:07:45,255 --> 00:07:47,223
Wes, I got a United States
senator waitin' for me...

111
00:07:47,324 --> 00:07:51,818
so just find out whatever you can about
this Boretz thing, and we'll talk later, okay?

112
00:07:56,166 --> 00:07:58,430
- "Small stuff."
<i>- Listen...</i>

113
00:07:58,535 --> 00:08:00,833
you need some Boretz killing
done, I'll have a go.

114
00:08:00,938 --> 00:08:03,998
I haven't had a decent tussle
since the blue meanie and I stopped sparring.

115
00:08:04,107 --> 00:08:06,905
<i>Yes. All right.</i>
<i>Call me if you find anything.</i>

116
00:08:07,010 --> 00:08:09,308
I'll be in my office,
learning what I can.

117
00:08:10,547 --> 00:08:12,606
