are important enough to avenge.

173
00:11:29,613 --> 00:11:33,777
I think corporate living's
made him lose his love for the hunt.

174
00:11:33,884 --> 00:11:36,751
No worries.
More for me then.

175
00:11:38,688 --> 00:11:41,088
[Illyria]
It does not serve his interest.

176
00:11:42,359 --> 00:11:44,691
What are you on about?

177
00:11:44,795 --> 00:11:47,889
I've seen this before
with many rulers.

178
00:11:49,466 --> 00:11:52,094
- Your leader has been corrupted.
<i>- Hey. Hang on.</i>

179
00:11:52,202 --> 00:11:54,466
In the first place,
Angel's not my leader.

180
00:11:54,571 --> 00:11:57,199
And in the second, what the bloody hell
do you mean, "corrupted"?

181
00:11:57,307 --> 00:12:00,174
It always begins the same.

182
00:12:00,277 --> 00:12:03,940
A ruler turns a blind eye to the dealings
or battles from which he cannot gain...

183
00:12:04,047 --> 00:12:07,210
<i>and a deaf ear to the counsel</i>
<i>of those closest to him.</i>

184
00:12:07,317 --> 00:12:10,878
As his strength increases, so does
the separation between him and his follow...

185
00:12:10,987 --> 00:12:13,285
Shh.

186
00:12:13,390 --> 00:12:16,689
- You smell that?
- The odors of everything in this world of men...

187
00:12:16,793 --> 00:12:19,057
are equally repugnant
to me.

188
00:12:19,162 --> 00:12:21,289
Bloody helpful.

189
00:12:25,402 --> 00:12:29,099
